# Environment Variables Template
#
# IMPORTANT: Copy this file to .env and fill in real values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# .env is in .gitignore — it will NEVER be committed to GitHub.
# Only .env.example (this file) is committed, with placeholder values.
#
# Why .env is gitignored:
# If .env reaches GitHub with real credentials, bots will find and exploit
# them within minutes. AWS charges of $3,200+ have been reported from a
# single leaked key. This single .gitignore rule prevents 89% of accidental
# secret leaks. (GitGuardian 2024)
#
# How to use:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Replace placeholder values with your real credentials
# 3. NEVER commit .env — it is automatically ignored by git
# 4. When you add a new variable, add a placeholder line HERE too
#    so other developers (and AI agents) know the variable exists.

# === Add your environment variables below ===
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/dbname
# API_KEY=your-api-key-here
# NODE_ENV=development
# PORT=3000
